{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow motorbike riders with a current CBT to get road experience without paying.",
        "additional_details": "The current law allows learner riders to get road experience on bikes over 125cc only by paying training centres to escort them, some cant afford this cost, and it makes motorcycling less inclusive.  I suggest a change in law to allow an experienced and minimum aged rider to escort them whilst gaining road skills before sitting the tests.",
        "background": "Change to current law to allow learner motorbike riders to ride test sized bikes on the road before sitting mod1/mod2 test without paying for training centres to escort them.",
